[0.005, "o", "\u001b[1;3HStart a new pool named 'www'.\u001b[2;2H the variable $pool can be used in any directive and will be replaced by the\r\n; pool name ('www' here)\r\n\u001b[96m[www]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[70X\r\n\u001b[71X\u001b[6;3HPer pool prefix\u001b[65X\u001b[7;3HIt only app\u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fes on the following directives:\u001b[17X\u001b[8;2H - 'access.log'\u001b[9;3H- 'slowlog'\u001b[8X\u001b[10;3H- '\u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten' (unixsocket)\u001b[59X\u001b[11;3H- 'chroot'\u001b[33X\u001b[12;3H- 'chdir'\u001b[73X\u001b[13;3H- 'php_values'\u001b[29X\u001b[14;3H- 'php_admin_values'\u001b[49X\u001b[15;3HWhen not set, the global prefix (or /usr) app\u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fes instead.\u001b[11X\u001b[16;3HNote: This directive can also be relative to the global prefix.\u001b[17;18Hnone\u001b[22X\u001b[18;3Hrefix = /path/to/pools/$pool    \u001b[20;3HUnix user/group of the child processes. This can be used only if the master  \u001b[21;3Hprocess running user is root. It is set after the child process is created.   \u001b[22;3HThe user and group can be specified either by their name or by their numeric\u001b[23;3HIDs.\u001b[47X\u001b[24;3HNote: If the user is root, the executable needs to be started with\u001b[6X\u001b[25;3H      --allow-to-run-as-root option to work.   \u001b[26;3HDefault Values: The user is set to master process running user by default.\u001b[27;9H          If the group is not set, the user's group is used.\u001b[11X\r\nuser =\u001b[92m http\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[31X\r\ngroup =\u001b[92m http\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[12X\r\n\u001b[18X\n; The address on which to accept FastCGI requests.\u001b[32;3HVa\u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fd syntaxes are:\u001b[56X\u001b[33;3H  'ip.add.re.ss:port'    - to \u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten on a TCP socket to a specific IPv4 address on\u001b[34;3H                           a specific port;\u001b[35;2H   '[ip:6:addr:ess]:port' - to \u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten on a TCP socket to a specific IPv6 address on\r\n;                            a specific port;\u001b[37;3H  'port'                 - to \u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten on a TCP socket to all addresses\u001b[38;3H                           (IPv6 and IPv4-mapped) on a specific port;\u001b[39;2H   '/path/to/unix/socket' - to \u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten on a unix socket.\r\n; Note: This value is mandatory.\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten =\u001b[92m /run/php-fpm/php-fpm.sock\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[33X\u001b[43;3HSet \u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten(2) backlog.\u001b[44;3HDefault Value: 511 (-1 on Linux, FreeBSD and OpenBSD)\u001b[45;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mli\u001b[m\u000fsten.backlog = 511\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f7,14           Top\u001b[48;4H\u001b[?25h"]
