[0.006, "o", "\u001b[2;3HServerAdmin: Your address, where problems with the server should be   \u001b[3;3He-mailed.  This address appears on some server-generated pages, such\u001b[6X\u001b[4;3Has error documents.  e.g. admin@your-domain.com\u001b[21X\u001b[5;2H\u001b[71X\r\n\u001b[96mServerAdmin\u001b[m\u000f you@\u001b[96mexample\u001b[m\u000f.com\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[8;2H\u001b[43X\r\n# ServerName gives the name and port that the server uses to identify itself.\u001b[10;2H This can often be determined automatically, but we recommend you specify\u001b[11;3Hit explicitly to prevent problems during startup.\u001b[17X\u001b[12;2H\u001b[46X\n If your host doesn't have a registered DNS name, enter its IP address here.\u001b[14;2H\u001b[67X\nServerName www.example.com:80\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[17;2H\u001b[71X\u001b[18;3HDeny access to the entirety of your server's filesystem. You must\u001b[19;2H explicitly permit access to web content directories in other \r\n# <Directory> blocks below.\r\n#\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<Directory\u001b[m\u000f /\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\r\n\u001b[m\u000f    \u001b[30m\u001b[103mAllowO\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mverride\u001b[m\u000f none\u001b[49X\r\n    \u001b[96mRequire\u001b[m\u000f all denied\u001b[33X\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f</Directory>\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[27;2H\u001b[75X\u001b[28;3HNote that from this point forward you must specifically allow\u001b[29;2H particular features to be enabled - so if something's not working as\u001b[30;3Hyou might expect, make sure that you have specifically enabled it\r\n# below.\r\n\n\u001b[67X\u001b[34;2H\u001b[58X\u001b[35;3HDocumentRoot: The directory out of which you will serve your\u001b[36;2H documents. By default, all requests are taken from this directory, but\u001b[37;3Hsymbolic links and aliases may be used to point to other locations.\u001b[38;2H\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[96mDocumentRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/srv/http\"\r\n\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f<Directory\u001b[m\u000f \"/srv/http\"\u001b[0;10;1m\u000f>\r\n\u001b[m\u000f    #    \r\n    # Possible values for the Options directive are \"None\", \"All\",\r\n    # or any combination of:\r\n    #   Indexes Includes FollowSymLinks SymLinksifOwnerMatch ExecCGI MultiViews\r\n    #\r\n    # Note that \"MultiViews\" must be named *explicitly* --- \"Options All\"\u001b[5X\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f239,5          43\u001b[48;8H\u001b[?25h"]
